Create EKS-cluster using aws-cli:
--------------------------------

*aws ecr get-login-password --region <region> | docker login --username AWS --password-stdin<aws-account-id>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com

*aws ecr create-repository 
--repository-name <name-repository> 
--image-scanning-configuration scanOnPush=true 
--region <region>

*sudo docker images

*docker tag <image-name:version> <repository uri>

*docker push <taged image-name>

*aws ecr batch-delete-image 
--repository-name <name-repository> 
--image-ids imageTag=<version>
--region <region>

* aws ecr delete-repository 
--repository-name <name-repository> 
--force 
--region <region>

Commands:
==========

   kubectl apply -f deploy.pod.yaml
   kubectl get rs
   kubectl get pods
   kubectl scale deployment deploy --replicas=5
   kubectl get pods
   kubectl set image deployment.app/deploy nginx=nginx:1.24.0
   kubectl get pods
   watch kubectl get pods
   kubectl set image deployment.app/deploy nginx=nginx:1.23
   watch kubectl get pods
   kubectl rollout status deployment deploy
   watch kubectl get pods
   kubectl rollout history deployment deploy
   kubectl rollout history deployment deploy --revision=3
   kubectl rollout undo deployment deploy
   kubectl rollout history deployment deploy --revision=3
   kubectl rollout history deployment deploy
   kubectl get pods
   kubectl rollout status deployment deploy
   kubectl describe deployment deploy
   kubectl rollout undo deployment deploy
   kubectl describe deployment deploy
   kubectl get pods
